      "note_no": "110",
      "note": "Regarding the expression \"bond with God\" ('ahd Allah), see surah 2, note 19. The clause \"whenever you bind yourselves by a pledge\" has a twofold meaning: in the first instance (as in 13:20) it refers to the spiritual, moral and social obligations arising from one's faith in God; and, secondly, it applies to all pledges or promises given by one person to another - for, as Razi points out, every pledge given by man to man represents, in its essence, a pledge to God. It is to this second aspect of man's \"bond with God\" that the sequence refers."
